<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,471,526]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<taxonomicName authority=": Lieftinck (1935)" authorityName=": Lieftinck" authorityYear="1935" box="[151,557,471,495]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis box="[151,371,471,495]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Drepanosticta tenella</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[386,557,471,495]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref15543" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1935) A Synopsis of the Odonata (Dragonflies) of Sumatra. Miscellanea Zoologica Sumatrana, 92 - 93, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1935">Lieftinck (1935)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: Original description of both sexes, “Gisting and environs”, Mount Tanggamus, 
<collectingRegion country="Indonesia" name="Lampung" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Lampung</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[263,350,502,526]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, p. 7, 
<figureCitation box="[410,470,502,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1410,192,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[166,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drepanosticta annandalei ♂ [a, c, e, g, h, i] &amp; ♀ [b, d, f, j], Bamboo Teri,Andaman Island, India (NZC). (a, b), head &amp; thorax, lateral view; (c), head, dorsal view; (d), synthorax, dorsal view; (e, f), terminal segments of abdomen, lateral view; (g–i) appendages in lateral, dorsal and ventral view; (j), pterostigma, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677827" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677827/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[483,654,502,526]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 202" refId="ref15575" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1954) Handlist of Malaysian Odonata. A catalogue of the dragonflies of the Malay Peninsula, Sumatra, Java and Borneo, including the adjacent small islands. Treubia, Supplement, 22, i-xiii + 1 - 202." type="journal article" year="1954">Lieftinck (1954)</bibRefCitation>
: Distribution (western 
<collectingRegion box="[885,969,502,526]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
added without details), habitat, p 37.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,572,1102]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,225,572,598]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[231,414,572,599]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref15543" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1935) A Synopsis of the Odonata (Dragonflies) of Sumatra. Miscellanea Zoologica Sumatrana, 92 - 93, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1935">Lieftinck (1935)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lieftinck" authorityYear="1935" box="[533,642,572,598]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis box="[533,642,572,598]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the south of 
<collectingRegion box="[843,939,572,598]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, giving illustrations of the male anal appendages in dorsal and lateral view. Unfortunately Lieftinck’s description is made largely by comparison to the earlier published description (
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[409,580,644,670]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="109 - 147" refId="ref15514" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1929) Contributions to the Dragonfly fauna of the Sondaic Area. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 72, 109 - 147." type="journal article" year="1929">Lieftinck 1929</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lieftinck, 1929" authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1929" box="[629,929,644,670]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gazella">
<emphasis box="[629,746,644,670]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. gazella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[755,929,644,670]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="109 - 147" refId="ref15514" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1929) Contributions to the Dragonfly fauna of the Sondaic Area. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 72, 109 - 147." type="journal article" year="1929">Lieftinck, 1929</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1001,1051,645,671]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Java</collectingRegion>
(which does not belong in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carmichaeli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. carmichaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group based on the structure of its posterior pronotal lobe, also see the discussion here). Later 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 202" refId="ref15575" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1954) Handlist of Malaysian Odonata. A catalogue of the dragonflies of the Malay Peninsula, Sumatra, Java and Borneo, including the adjacent small islands. Treubia, Supplement, 22, i-xiii + 1 - 202." type="journal article" year="1954">Lieftinck (1954)</bibRefCitation>
added the west of 
<collectingRegion box="[433,526,716,742]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
to the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lieftinck" authorityYear="1935" box="[766,875,716,742]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis box="[766,875,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without giving any details. The illustrations of the anal appendages of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lieftinck" authorityYear="1935" box="[377,488,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis box="[377,488,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[527,713,752,779]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref15543" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1935) A Synopsis of the Odonata (Dragonflies) of Sumatra. Miscellanea Zoologica Sumatrana, 92 - 93, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1935">Lieftinck (1935)</bibRefCitation>
show cerci conforming to our definition of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1931" box="[1258,1427,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carmichaeli">
<emphasis box="[1258,1427,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. carmichaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group (in fact resembling those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Phan &amp; Yokoi &amp; Makbun &amp; Joshi &amp; Subramanian &amp; Ngo &amp; Dow, 2021" authorityName="Phan &amp; Yokoi &amp; Makbun &amp; Joshi &amp; Subramanian &amp; Ngo &amp; Dow" authorityYear="2021" box="[544,714,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wildermuthi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[544,714,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. wildermuthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[722,813,788,815]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,807,788,814]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in lateral view) and also paraprocts conforming to the group, with a clear subbasal spur visible in both dorsal and lateral views. Although parts of the paraprocts are not visible in Lieftinck’s illustrations he states that they are “shaped much as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1929" box="[986,1067,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gazella">
<emphasis box="[986,1067,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">gazella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” and the paraprocts of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1929" box="[1322,1436,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gazella">
<emphasis box="[1322,1436,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. gazella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack any character to distinguish it from the species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1931" box="[803,971,896,922]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carmichaeli">
<emphasis box="[803,971,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. carmichaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. The prothorax of both sexes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lieftinck" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also conforms to the definition of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1931" box="[667,836,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carmichaeli">
<emphasis box="[667,836,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. carmichaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group and we therefore include it in that group. The genital ligula of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lieftinck" authorityYear="1935" box="[334,444,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis box="[334,444,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been illustrated. Based on the measurements provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[1180,1364,968,995]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref15543" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1935) A Synopsis of the Odonata (Dragonflies) of Sumatra. Miscellanea Zoologica Sumatrana, 92 - 93, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1935">Lieftinck (1935)</bibRefCitation>
this is the smallest member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1931" box="[459,626,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carmichaeli">
<emphasis box="[459,626,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">D. carmichaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. However these measurements are from a single population and it is very likely that greater variation would be found if additional specimens were measured.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
